c({"name": "can.ui.layout.Resize", "type": "class", "comment": "<p>Adds a resizable hook to the bottom right of an element \nallowing you to drag the handle to resize the element. This can be\nuseful for expanding <code>textarea</code>s or implementing a resizable window\nsystem.</p>\n\n<h1>Example</h1>\n\n<p>Given the following markup:</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;label&gt;\n    &lt;textarea id=\"comment\" name=\"comment\"&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;\n&lt;/label&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>As well as the following css:</p>\n\n<pre><code>.ui-resizable-handle {\n    display: block;\n    font-size: 0.1px;\n    position: absolute;\n    z-index: 1000;\n}\n\n.ui-resizable-s {\n    bottom: -3px;\n    cursor: s-resize;\n    height: 7px;\n    left: 0;\n    width: 100%;\n}\n.ui-resizable-e {\n    cursor: e-resize;\n    height: 100%;\n    right: -3px;\n    top: 0;\n    width: 7px;\n\n}\n.ui-resizable-se {\n    bottom: 0px;\n    cursor: se-resize;\n    height: 12px;\n    right: 0px;\n    width: 12px;\n    background-color: #ddddff;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You can make the textarea resizable using the following code:</p>\n\n<pre><code>$(\"textarea\").can_ui_layout_resize({\n    minHeight : 40,\n    minWidth: 120\n});\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This adds three small <code>div</code>s to the element. One to the lower right\ncorner, one to the bottom edge and one to the right edge. These\ndivs become draggable hooks that allow you to resize the element.\nTo style these elements, simply over ride the above css.</p>\n\n<p>When resizing the initialized element, it emits the \"resize\" event.</p>\n\n<h2>Demo</h2>\n\n<div class='demo_wrapper' data-demo-src='canui/layout/resize/resize.html'></div>", "parents": ["canui"], "test": "canui/layout/resize/funcunit.html", "description": "Makes an element resizable.", "params": {"options": {"order": 0, "description": "<p>Object literal defining the minimum height\nand width the element should be allowed to be resized to.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>minHeight</code> - The minimum height the element will be allowed to\nresize to.</li>\n<li><code>minWidth</code> - The minimum width the element will be allowed to\nresize to.</li>\n</ul>", "name": "options", "type": "Object", "optional": false}}, "src": "canui/layout/resize/resize.js", "line": 25, "children": ["can.ui.layout.Resize.defaults", "can.ui.layout.Resize.init"]})